    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-04-02T00:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-04-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="700"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d700">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/4951: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="#p_JNT1" type="from"
                            >Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-04-02T13:00:00+08:00"
                            >April 2, 1932—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 2—6:10 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>My March 31, 1 p.m.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Negotiators met this morning at 10 a.m. and within a short time adopted
                        the last paragraph of annex 1 to read: <quote rend="blockquote">
                            <p>“In the event of doubt arising in regard thereto the positions in
                                question will be ascertained upon the request of the joint
                                commission by representatives of the participating friendly powers
                                members of the joint high commission.”</p>
                        </quote>
                    </item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Last paragraph of paragraph 3 also accepted in the same wording.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>Last paragraph of annex 4 accepted to read: <quote rend="blockquote">
                            <p>“The commission will in accordance with its decision watch in such
                                manner as it deems best the carrying out of the provisions of
                                articles 1, 2 and 3, of this agreement.[”]</p>
                        </quote>
                    </item>
                    <label>4.</label>
                    <item>Discussion then proceeded to taking up article 3 and that 2 [<hi
                            rend="italic">annex 3?</hi>] and it was agreed to carry this question
                        over until next meeting as the Japanese were awaiting instructions from
                        Tokyo.</item>
                    <label>5.</label>
                    <item>Meeting adjourned until Monday, April 4th, at 3 p.m.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_JNT1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
